Generally, I really love Tipsy Pig. The white-haired staff are awesome and love dogs, and the food is excellent. Unlike at other karaoke places, you do not rent the room but instead put a dollar in the machine every time you want to sing a song, so it's good for people who like to take breaks or talk story between songs instead of feeling like you have to sing constantly to get your money's worth for the room. Two caveats: the machine has this annoying whistling piccolo-like sound that tells you what melody to sing, and there's no way to turn it off. I want to hear my voice singing the melody, not some whistling robot. Also, the black-haired guy with the tattoos is a terrible waiter: he forgot what we asked for and then insisted we never asked for it, only deigning to apologize after he found our order sitting on the counter in the kitchen area. Plus, he called me ma'am, and I'm clearly a gorgeous *young* hottie in a pretty dress, not an old aunty in an apron. Even my friend was shocked. Dude needs to learn some manners from his white-haired colleagues! Otherwise, much love for Tipsy Pig. We will be back many times.
